headline.main: NAVY BASE BOMBED; Palermo Also Is a Target as British Range Far in Fascist Empire ERITREAN CAMP IS FIRED Bardia Area Raided -- Ground Patrols Go 75 Miles Inside Libya, Near Tobruk

lead_paragraph: CAIRO, Egypt, Jan. 1 -- In a series of raids over a vast area extending from lower Italy to Libya and to the southern gate of the Red Sea, British pilots have bombed half a dozen points vital to the Fascist war machine, the Royal Air Force announced today.
